modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve error messages from error code values. Works with a custom type `t` representing specific error codes. Used to generate human-readable diagnostics from internal error representations.

Provides password hashing with Argon2i using specified memory and time costs, and parallelism, returning raw or encoded hash values. Supports verification of passwords against encoded strings and conversion of hash values to string representations. Designed for secure password storage and authentication workflows.

Provides functions to hash passwords using Argon2d with customizable parameters, verify hashed passwords, and convert hash values between internal representations and strings. Operates on string passwords, salts, and specialized hash types for raw and encoded outputs. Used to securely store and validate user credentials in authentication systems.

Provides functions to hash passwords using the Argon2id algorithm with customizable parameters, verify passwords against encoded hashes, and convert hash values to strings. Operates on string passwords, salts, and specialized hash types for raw and encoded outputs. Used to securely store and validate user credentials in authentication systems.

Generates and verifies cryptographic hashes using the Argon2 algorithm. Accepts passwords, salts, and configuration parameters to produce secure hash outputs. Used for password storage and authentication in security-sensitive applications.

Handles password hashing with configurable cost parameters, producing either raw or encoded hash values. Accepts password and salt strings, returning results in specific types for secure storage or comparison. Provides verification and conversion utilities for hash representations.
